1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,080
Mm.

2
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:14,920
You're finally here?

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,280
I've been waiting for an hour.

4
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:20,560
The professor tore my work apart.

5
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:23,240
Yours is still lucky.
You just have to fix it.

6
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:27,400
Mine? No fixes at all.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,920
You have to redo everything?

8
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:34,520
Yeah.

9
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:38,360
You promised to help me. Help me.

10
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:41,280
Of course I will. We're friends.
How could I not?

11
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,240
Come on.

12
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:45,040
- Really?
- Oh, please.

13
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:49,560
As long as I've got you, I'm not scared.
Redo it? Fine, I'll redo it.

14
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:52,640
Just watch.
I'll be the first to submit in class.

15
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:58,240
I'm hungry. What should we eat?

16
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:04,120
Lak.

17
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:11,160
What's wrong?

18
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,760
Uh…

19
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:15,520
Lak.

20
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,280
You saw something again, didn't you?

21
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:20,440
Please don't get hurt.

22
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:23,280
I'll take you to make merit, okay?

23
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,640
Again?

24
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,760
You saw that I'm going to die again?

25
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:36,520
Am I really going to die?

26
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,480
Lak…

27
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,480
Lak, I love you.

28
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:46,760
It's okay.
I'll take you to make merit, alright?

29
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,400
You're going to be fine.

30
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,000
Why are you apologizing to her?

31
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:28,320
I know what I'm doing.

32
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,760
Even if she had nothing to do
with Ms. Lak's death,

33
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:34,320
how do you know
whether Ms. Lak hated Kluay or not?

34
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,320
I don't care about that.

35
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,600
Why are you wasting time on this

36
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,200
instead of dealing with Warat?

37
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,000
<i>What are you really thinking, Mr. Sin?</i>

38
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:46,880
I'm going to take everything back.
Everything that should be mine.

39
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,760
Oh.

40
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,840
Where's Mr. Jirasin?

41
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,960
Uh, he already left.

42
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,440
Madam wants to see you.

43
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,600
- Me?
- Yes, this way.

44
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:27,800
Kluay.

45
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,600
Have you been waiting long?

46
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,960
Oh.

47
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:35,880
Not at all. I just got here.

48
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,000
Order whatever you like, food or drinks.

49
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,920
- Yes?
- Yes. It's on me.

50
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,760
No, it's okay, Sin.
You don't have to treat me.

51
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,960
No, let me…

52
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,160
I really want to apologize.

53
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,920
There's no problem about that.

54
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,120
I understand everything.

55
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:59,760
If I were you, I'd probably feel the same.

56
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:02,560
Thank you for understanding me.

57
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:07,800
Menu, please.

58
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,600
Was it far?

59
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,200
Not really.

60
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,920
Thanks for coming.

61
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,160
Please have a seat.

62
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,600
Yes.

63
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,240
Mrs. Wanee, is there something urgent?

64
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:39,520
Yes. Explain.

65
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,920
- I knew it.
- Knew what?

66
00:06:57,280 --> 00:07:00,320
Since we're here, let me speak honestly.

67
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,520
Mr. Arnon.

68
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,080
What exactly are you trying to do to me?

69
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:11,000
Anyone can tell from these documents
that Mr. Warat's files

70
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,600
were fabricated

71
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:16,760
to make it look like Mr. Jirasin and I
have been embezzling from Vanich Mall.

72
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:19,480
But if you compare them
with the real records,

73
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:22,640
it's obvious that Mr. Warat's set is fake.

74
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,960
Why? You want us gone, don't you?

75
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,160
Did a competitor
hire you to destroy Vanich?

76
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,560
How much did they pay you,
Mr. Arnon, to go this far?

77
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,840
Mrs. Wanee.

78
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,840
You see? Arnon was hired
by a competitor to destroy us.

79
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,520
No wonder Mr. Jirasin kept telling me

80
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,840
someone was targeting Mr. Warat.

81
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,560
Who would've thought
it was someone close to us.

82
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,160
Mrs. Wanee,

83
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:53,480
one night, the CCTV footage
completely disappeared.

84
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,080
What are you trying to say?

85
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,040
But luckily, the hidden camera I set up

86
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,680
wasn't affected.

87
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,520
What's in the footage?

88
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,760
Just a moment.

89
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,680
Here it is.

90
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:21,200
Explain. Who is this man?

91
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:26,000
Oh, he's a programmer.
That day, the system…

92
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:29,240
What kind of programmer
would be in the accounting room?

93
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:35,159
- Well, I…
- And why would a programmer come in

94
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,600
on the exact day
the CCTV system went down?

95
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,200
I was following Mr. Jirasin's orders.

96
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,840
Now we know

97
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,480
which documents are real

98
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,760
and which ones are fabricated.

99
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,600
- Mrs. Wanee, I…
- Go pack your things.

100
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,360
Yes.

101
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:06,240
You heard her. Go.

102
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:11,720
Mrs. Wanee, please.
Everything was a competitor's plan.

103
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,840
Competitors can't destroy Vanich.

104
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,120
The ones who can

105
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:20,040
are you two.

106
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,320
Get out.

107
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,600
Or do you want to sit here

108
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,720
until the police arrive?

109
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:03,280
Yes, any updates?

110
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:07,640
<i>Hello, Mr. Supol.</i>
<i>Have you heard of Baan Saeng Wan Mai?</i>

111
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,840
Yes.

112
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:14,040
<i>I've got credible information</i>
<i>that Ms. Waree might still be alive.</i>

113
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,360
What?

114
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,720
<i>The person who helped Ms. Waree back then</i>
<i>was Mr. Pichai,</i>

115
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,920
<i>the founder of Baan Saeng Wan Mai.</i>

116
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,160
Understood.

117
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,520
Oh, Mr. Warat.

118
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

119
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:51,200
Mr. Warat, Mr. Arnon and Som
have been looking everywhere for you.

120
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,800
Mama Toi.

121
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,520
I need to ask you something important.

122
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,600
Oh.

123
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,920
What is it?

124
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:04,960
Do you have any photos of Kluay
when she was a child?

125
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:14,480
Mr. Warat,
sorry for asking something personal,

126
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:19,640
but is it true
that you broke up with Kluay?

127
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,280
Mrs. Wanee, if everything's settled,
I'll take my leave.

128
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,320
That's another one dealt with.

129
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:38,840
You already knew, didn't you?

130
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:43,160
I've spent my whole life
with these documents.

131
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:47,280
One glance is enough
to tell what's real and what's fake.

132
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,000
Then why let them continue?

133
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,080
I didn't want to be too harsh on Jirasin.

134
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,320
Why not?

135
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:02,400
If there's something I can give him,
I'd rather give it.

136
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:09,840
You giving it to him and him stealing it
are two very different things.

137
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,520
All this time,

138
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:16,240
it's not that I didn't know.

139
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:21,400
I just chose to look the other way.

140
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,800
Because you pitied him?

141
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:34,720
With the utmost respect, ma'am,
I have new information to report.

142
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:35,720
What is it?

143
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,640
Ms. Waree might still be alive.

144
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,840
You found her? Are there any new leads?

145
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,720
Where is my granddaughter now?

146
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,160
- Supol?
- Well, ma'am.

147
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:56,160
All leads point to
Baan Saeng Wan Mai, ma'am.

148
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,880
Just a moment.

149
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:09,640
- Well, Kluay.
- Yes?

150
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:13,320
I need to take this call.
I'll be right back.

151
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,920
Of course, take your time. Don't worry.

152
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,920
I'm not in a hurry.

153
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,520
Order whatever you like, don't hold back.

154
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,080
Alright.

155
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,880
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

156
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,240
What is it?

157
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,800
<i>Arnon's made his move against us.</i>

158
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,560
Arnon? That useless guy?
What could he possibly do to us?

159
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,880
<i>Mrs. Wanee already fired me.</i>

160
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,360
What did he do for Mom to fire you?

161
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:47,800
That day when I brought someone
to alter the data at the office.

162
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:51,680
I already had the CCTV footage erased.

163
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,800
What could he possibly see?

164
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,920
Arnon had another hidden camera.

165
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,000
Then what are you going to do?

166
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:03,840
You take the blame first.
As long as I'm still here,

167
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:06,920
I can still help you. But if I get
fired too, we're both finished.

168
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:08,840
Is there any other way?

169
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:12,520
I told you. Take the blame yourself.
Take it all.

170
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:15,280
Mr. Sin, we're broke now, aren't we?

171
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,520
The shares are gone,
and we already returned all the money.

172
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:20,720
Calm down. Get a grip.

173
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,440
Just endure it a little longer.

174
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:36,080
I'll finish everything myself.

175
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,640
Just watch.

176
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,400
Have you found
the important documents yet?

177
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,240
Not yet.

178
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,480
Um…

179
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:13,040
Did Kluay do something to upset you?

180
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,000
No, not really.

181
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,280
Then what's wrong with my daughter?

182
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,440
To me,

183
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,880
Kluay is a very good person.

184
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:35,280
Or is it because she's just an orphan,

185
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,720
not suitable for…

186
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,160
That has nothing to do with it.

187
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,200
I'm an orphan too.

188
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:45,640
The man I thought was my father…

189
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,680
wasn't my father, and the man I hated

190
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,800
turned out to be my real father.

191
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,680
Uh…

192
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,680
Can you tell me about it?

193
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,240
Well.

194
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,840
I love Kluay.

195
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,880
No matter who she is,

196
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,240
whether she's an orphan

197
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:20,440
or whatever her status is,

198
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,280
I love her for who she is.

199
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,640
No matter what happens,
I will always love her.

200
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:30,360
If you love each other,
then why did you break up?

201
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,720
Because I'm bad luck.

202
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,520
Ever since she's been with me,

203
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:43,560
she's had to go through…

204
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,360
a lot of things.

205
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,280
She's been attacked,

206
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,600
drugged,

207
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:55,400
and recently, she…

208
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,760
What happened recently?

209
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,960
She started having signs about herself.

210
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:08,680
I love her so much.

211
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,160
No matter what happens,

212
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:19,400
I don't want her to be in danger.

213
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:24,280
So I did everything. Even if it hurts me,

214
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:28,359
I have to let her go.

215
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:34,480
I understand now.

216
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,440
But if that's the case,

217
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:40,760
you should stay even closer to her.

218
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:46,400
So many things have happened,

219
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,320
but every time something went wrong,

220
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:52,600
weren't you the one who protected her?

221
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,480
If you two love each other,

222
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:59,600
you should hold on
to each other even tighter.

223
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:04,000
If you know the one you love is in danger,

224
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:08,400
do you step in to protect them
or do you walk away?

225
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,080
You're right.

226
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,760
I understand now.

227
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,440
I'm the one…

228
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:20,960
who was wrong.

229
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,040
Wait.

230
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,280
This photo…

231
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:36,240
What did that investigator say?

232
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:39,640
He said the person who took the child in
was Mr. Pichai.

233
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,600
Mr. Pichai was Mama Toi's husband,

234
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,240
but he passed away…

235
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,440
When did he die?

236
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,920
About 25 years ago.

237
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,360
Twenty-five years…

238
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:54,800
That's around
the same time Ampha disappeared.

239
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,640
Yes.

240
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,600
Have you contacted Ms. Kluay yet?

241
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,920
She said she went out to eat.
She told me to pick her up after.

242
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,800
Do you know where Mr. Warat is?

243
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:14,080
Not sure. I can't reach him at all.

244
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,480
His phone's been off all day.

245
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:19,520
Where could he have gone? I have no idea.

246
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,480
That's strange.
He's not where he should be.

247
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,120
Where could he be?

248
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:33,280
I know what you are thinking.

249
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,560
Part of me

250
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:41,720
wants to find Waree more than anything.

251
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,480
Because Waree is my grandchild.

252
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,200
A grandchild

253
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:51,720
I must love and cherish,

254
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:53,960
just as

255
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,800
I've always loved you.

256
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:02,640
I pray that I can find Waree

257
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:08,080
because the first thing
I want to say to her is

258
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,040
"Come back and live with me."

259
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:13,600
"From now on,

260
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:17,120
it will just be the three of us,
grandmother and grandchildren."

261
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:22,240
As for you,

262
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,480
no matter how many times I say it,

263
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,840
I'll always mean the same thing.

264
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,960
Whether

265
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,480
you carry my blood

266
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:38,000
or not at all,

267
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:41,840
you are still my beloved grandson.

268
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,520
And no one,

269
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:50,160
no one can change my heart

270
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:54,080
or the truth of my life.

271
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:58,240
And most importantly,

272
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:03,280
I know… I know that

273
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:07,720
the sooner I find Waree,

274
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,000
the sooner you,

275
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,640
my beloved grandson,

276
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:16,680
will no longer have to worry.

277
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,480
Isn't that right?

278
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,680
Actually,
I've already found Waree, Grandma.

279
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:32,520
You found her? Who is she?

280
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,280
Who is Waree?

281
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,000
She's been with us all along.

282
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,800
Take a look

283
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:02,920
at the anklet
on that little girl in the photo.

284
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,600
Oh my…

285
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,840
That means…

286
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,080
the anklet…

287
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:20,480
and that girl…

288
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:23,960
- is…
- Waree is Kluay.

289
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,080
She's Ms. Ampha's only daughter.

290
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,280
That means…

291
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:41,040
she's your real granddaughter.

292
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:46,800
Then where is Waree now?

293
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,200
Is she at home?

294
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,560
She is, isn't she?

295
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,600
Kluay is Waree? Mr. Warat, Arnon,

296
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:57,480
let's go bring her home.

297
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,920
Thank you.

298
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,360
Kluay.

299
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:19,840
I want to apologize to you.
A proper apology.

300
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,760
It's okay.

301
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,080
I've never been angry at you.

302
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:32,760
I understand what it's like
to lose someone.

303
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:37,400
From now on, I want you
to see me as your brother.

304
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:42,120
If anything ever happens, I want to be
the first person you think of.

305
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:44,880
Okay.

306
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,920
Thank you, Sin.

307
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:52,120
- Your phone.
- Oh.

308
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:55,240
- Excuse me for a moment.
- Okay.

309
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:23,080
Kluay, are you with Jirasin right now?

310
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:26,040
<i>Yes, but you can come pick me up now.</i>

311
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,760
Okay, wait there.

312
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,200
Som.

313
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:33,600
Actually, Sin is a really good person.

314
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:36,560
It's such a shame
we misunderstood each other for so long.

315
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,760
Just wait a moment, okay?

316
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:41,520
I'm on my way. Don't go anywhere.

317
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:45,040
Alright. Just tell me when you're close.

318
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:57,040
Well, Sin,

319
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,440
I'll have to leave soon.

320
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:03,200
Of course. After we finish eating,

321
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,560
do you want me to take you home?

322
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:06,360
No, it's okay.

323
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:09,480
Som and Mr. Arnon just called.
They said they're almost here.

324
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,560
That way, you won't have to detour.

325
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,320
Alright.

326
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:21,440
Kluay, there's something I want to ask…

327
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:25,320
Uh, that day…

328
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:29,160
what really happened to Lak?

329
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:35,800
Sure.

330
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:39,720
I'll tell you everything.

331
00:25:57,200 --> 00:26:00,000
The professor told me to revise my work.

332
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,400
Where? What needs revising?

333
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,840
The professor didn't like the concept.

334
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,280
Didn't like the concept?

335
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,640
So that means

336
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,000
you have to redo everything.

337
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:13,280
Hey, don't say that.

338
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,920
It's okay. I'll help you.

339
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,720
- It's cute.
- Yeah, it's really cute. Look.

340
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,240
- The professor doesn't get it.
- Right. They never understand us.

341
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:26,320
- So you have to redo it.
- No, don't say that.

342
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,960
- I'm kidding. Come on.
- Ugh.

343
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:32,360
Let's go eat first, then,

344
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,320
we'll come back and work on it.

345
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:37,400
Yeah, I'm hungry too. What should we eat?

346
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:41,280
- Noodles?
- No, I just had that yesterday.

347
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,560
Mookata? Huh?

348
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,400
No, save that for dinner.

349
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,960
We can have it for lunch.

350
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:51,520
No. Mookata is for dinner.
I don't want to wash my hair.

351
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:54,080
As if you usually shower anyway.

352
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,280
Oh.

353
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:20,080
Kluay. Kluay.

354
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,120
Kluay.

355
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,720
You saw something again, didn't you?

356
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:30,040
Lak, stay still.

357
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:34,160
Don't move. Don't go down the stairs.

358
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:37,000
We'll go another way.

359
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:03,000
Lak.

360
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,040
Lak! Lak!

361
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:08,280
Ouch!

362
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:47,560
Sin.

363
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,480
Lak.

364
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,680
Lak. Lak.

365
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,200
Lak. Lak.

366
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,440
Lak.

367
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,000
Kluay.

368
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:17,600
Are you trying to tell me Lak fell down
the stairs because a ghost pushed her?

369
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:21,880
Yes, Sin.

370
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:25,240
I'm sorry.

371
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:31,880
I'm really sorry I couldn't save her.

372
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:34,640
That day, I…

373
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:42,680
I was so close to giving in.

374
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:46,920
Nice try. You were close.
Really, so close.

375
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,560
SOM

376
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,200
Pick up, Kluay. Pick up.

377
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,360
We're almost there, Mr. Warat.
Ten minutes.

378
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:12,680
Mr. Warat, watch out!

379
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:17,480
Come on, Kluay.

380
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:21,200
How could you go meet Jirasin?

381
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:32,440
SOM

382
00:30:45,320 --> 00:30:46,320
Mr. Warat.

383
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:50,520
Hey, that's Jirasin's car.

384
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,720
Kluay. He must have taken Kluay.

385
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,400
She's not answering. What do we do?

386
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:04,520
He definitely took Ms. Kluay.

387
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:07,560
- Call him.
- Who do you mean?

388
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,200
Jirasin. Call him.

389
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:15,200
Just as I thought.

390
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:18,680
Hello.

391
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:20,960
Mr. Arnon, put it on speaker.

392
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,680
We can talk this through.

393
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:29,040
Jirasin, bring Kluay back right now.

394
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:31,800
Kluay is at the restaurant.
How would she be with me?

395
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:32,880
Don't play games.

396
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,360
Your girlfriend is at the restaurant.
Go check if you don't believe me.

397
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:38,920
If you don't stop, I'll crash into you.

398
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,200
Be careful.

399
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,080
Mr. Warat, watch out!

400
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:09,880
Hey! You want trouble?
How do you even drive?

401
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,480
Watch the road!

402
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:15,240
- Sorry.
- Good, you got out. Where are you going?

403
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:17,360
- Hey. Let's talk first.
- Sorry.

404
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:22,480
- How are we settling this? How?
- Jirasin, what's going on?

405
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:23,880
<i>Pathetic.</i>

406
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,960
Why is this taking so long?

407
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:16,640
Hello, what seems to be the issue?

408
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:19,640
I already reported
that my girlfriend was kidnapped.

409
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,960
How do you know she was kidnapped?

410
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,320
- Calm down.
- Okay, fine.

411
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,480
- I will…
- Okay. It's alright.

412
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,640
You can explain everything to me.

413
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:28,880
- Well…
- I'll explain.

414
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,240
- I'll say it.
- Alright.

415
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,880
Waree…

416
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:44,320
The only granddaughter
of the Vanich family,

417
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,480
the one who destroyed our family.

418
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,360
Mom, Lak,

419
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:59,240
I'll take everything back for our family.

420
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:11,280
Between your child and that kid,
who will you choose?

421
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:13,320
Naree, listen to me first.

422
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,320
What was
that fatherless child's name again?

423
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,600
Naree, don't say that.

424
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:19,360
Warat, right?

425
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:21,480
If you love him so much, go raise him.

426
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:25,280
And remember this.
He's the one who destroyed everything.

427
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,400
He destroyed our family.

428
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:29,040
Waree,

429
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:32,080
the only granddaughter
of the Vanich family,

430
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:36,159
the one who destroyed everything
in our family.

431
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:42,800
Mom, Lak,

432
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,960
I'll take everything back for our family.

433
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:01,360
Waree,

434
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,760
are you happy?

435
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:10,840
Our child will inherit
everything from the Vanich family.

436
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:20,560
Yes, Mr. Supol?

437
00:35:20,640 --> 00:35:22,960
<i>Mr. Warat, have you found Ms. Waree?</i>

438
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:26,120
The police are tracking Jirasin's car now.

439
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,400
We should find them soon.

440
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:29,160
<i>If it's taking this long…</i>

441
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:33,160
At least Jirasin
probably won't dare kill Kluay.

442
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:36,000
<i>- Madam!</i>
- What?

443
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:37,360
Mr. Supol, what happened?

444
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:40,560
<i>Madam! Madam!</i>

445
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,720
What happened to Grandma?

446
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:44,040
<i>I'll take her to the hospital first.</i>

447
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:47,160
- Hey, wait… I'll…
<i>- It's alright.</i>

448
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:50,800
<i>You focus on finding Ms. Waree.</i>
<i>I'll handle this side.</i>

449
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:58,080
Mr. Warat, we found CCTV footage.

450
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:00,920
- Let's see it.
- This way, please.

451
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:10,440
Why is the car circling the same area
to make sure the cameras see it?

452
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,840
He planned this.

453
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,280
Mr. Arnon,

454
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:16,200
what do you think…

455
00:36:17,680 --> 00:36:19,160
he wants from Kluay?

456
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:20,800
That's the question.

457
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:24,720
Could it be revenge for Lakkana?

458
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,560
No, Som.

459
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,320
Ameena already said Lakkana's death

460
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,920
had nothing to do with Kluay.

461
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,240
- Hey. What happened here?
- Hm?

462
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:39,280
After this point,
the CCTV cameras were broken.

463
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:56,400
Transfer the money,
and I'll tell you where she is.

464
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:01,080
- Done.
- <i>Now we can talk.</i>

465
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:03,280
And you come alone. Don't try anything.

466
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:04,360
Fine.

467
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:27,400
What is this, Sin?

468
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:30,960
You're awake?

469
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:37,080
What did you do?

470
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:40,080
What do you think I did?

471
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,440
That can't be true.

472
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,080
You don't remember at all?

473
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:58,200
That can't be true.

474
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,920
<i>The one who lost dignity is you,</i>

475
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:18,440
using such dirty tactics on a woman.

476
00:38:18,520 --> 00:38:20,040
NEXT EPISODE

477
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:22,640
We have to trust Mr. Warat.
And we have to believe in him.

478
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:26,920
Because there's something
we need to finish first.

479
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:30,720
We have to settle everything

480
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:33,160
before Wanee wakes up.

481
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,040
Please take care of Grandma for me.

482
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:41,040
What do you mean?

483
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:46,000
<i>I should do more good things for Sin.</i>

484
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,080
Don't worry.

485
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:52,040
You'll get to do
something good for Sin soon.

486
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:18,720
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
